==English==
===Proper Noun===
'''God Almighty'''
# [[almighty]] [[God]]

====Synonyms====
* the [[Almighty]]

===Interjection===
'''God Almighty!'''
# an [[exclamation]] of [[surprise]] or [[astonishment]]
# How [[annoying]]! [[That's enough]]!
# (drawn, with little emphasis, last syllable held at same tone as penultimate; spoken with either resignation or spite) Oh no! I don't want this [[burden]]. I wish I didn't have to [[put up with]] this.
====Usage Note====
: Using the name of God in vain is considered swearing.
====Synonyms====
'''Burden'''
* [[Good grief]]!